</paragraph>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF838604FF0C5499FE16FE51" blockId="1.[151,1436,1558,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF838604FF0C5499FEE5FF99" box="[199,260,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF838604FEDA5499FEBCFF99" box="[273,349,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF838604FEA25499FE66FF99" box="[361,391,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">2a</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellow; labium and labrum brown; base of mandibles and genae pale, apex of mandibles black; antefrons pale yellow; vertex and remainder of head black, except for a curved pale yellow stripe connecting lateral ocelli with the antennae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="45AD665EFF808607FF5C5662FBFFFD34" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6405120" box="[151,1054,1073,1098]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" startId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" targetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF5C5662FBFFFD34" blockId="2.[151,1054,1073,1098]" box="[151,1054,1073,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FF5C5662FEF2FD34" bold="true" box="[151,275,1073,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF808607FED25661FDFCFD34" authority="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela, 2022" authorityName="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,541,1073,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calafatiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FED25661FDFCFD34" box="[281,541,1073,1097]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Heteragrion calafatiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FDE85661FD95FD37" bold="true" box="[547,628,1074,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="389557BFFF808607FDE85661FD95FD37" box="[547,628,1074,1098]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF0C56CFFE4CFCF3" blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FF0C56CFFEF9FDCB" box="[199,280,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF808607FEE356CFFE97FDCB" box="[296,374,1180,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF808607FE4F56CFFE40FDCA" box="[388,417,1180,1207]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">2b</figureCitation>
). Prothorax mostly yellow, lighter-colored laterally, with darker tones on dorsal areas: one brown stripe on each side of midline and another medial one; hind lobe rounded, mostly dark brown with yellow lateral stripes. Pterothorax with a black middorsal carina, and a thin pale yellow humeral stripe; mesepisternum mostly orange with a dark posterior spot; mesopleural suture pale yellow; mesepimeron dark orange; upper half of metepisternum pale yellow, remainder orange; remainder of pterothorax pale, except for a thin orange stripe on metepimeron. Coxae and trochanter pale yellow; femora alternating pale yellow and dark brown areas; tibiae brown; tarsi dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF0C57CBFBC6FCAB" blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FF0C57CBFEEAFCCC" box="[199,267,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF808607FED157CBFEBBFCCF" box="[282,346,1432,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, almost reaching S6 when closed; venation black, Pt dark brown; Pt overlying 3 cells in all wings, oblique proximally; 2 Pq cells in all wings; 18 Px in FW, 16 Px in HW.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF0C57B3FBBEFF1B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FF0C57B3FED0FC87" box="[199,305,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF808607FE8857B3FE77FC87" box="[323,406,1504,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[151,1436,179,1047]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov. male holotype from Pará, Brazil: habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405120/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). S1 pale yellow, with darker tones laterally and dorsally; S2 black dorsally, pale yellow laterally; S3–6 black with medially interrupted pale yellow basal rings and pale yellow medial stripes; S7 black with a thick medially interrupted pale yellow basal ring and a roughly quadrangular spot medially; S8–9 mostly black, pale yellow areas laterally; S10 orange laterally, with black borders and black dorsum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF0C5423FB3FFFAF" blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FF0C5423FE69FFF7" box="[199,392,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Anal appendages</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF808607FE5E5423FDEFFFF6" box="[405,526,1648,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Figs. 2c–d</figureCitation>
). Cercus dark brown with darker coloration especially on apex, carinas and spines; ventrobasal expansion absent; MP rounded, platelike morphology, rounded apex; ScP forming a small ridge bearing 4–5 denticles. Paraprocts pale yellow, posteriorly oriented, not reaching 1/2 of cercus, acute apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF0C548FFC68FF8B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" box="[199,905,1756,1782]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Measurements. FW 21.6; HW 20.9; Abdomen 32.3; Total 39.6.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF808607FF0C5553FE43FE67" blockId="2.[151,1437,1180,1818]" box="[199,418,1792,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF808607FF0C5553FEC4FE67" bold="true" box="[199,293,1792,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="45AD665EFF818606FF5C5471FA92FFFF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" startId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" targetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF818606FF5C5471FA92FFFF" blockId="3.[151,1437,1570,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FF5C5471FEF0FF47" bold="true" box="[151,273,1570,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FEDE5470FDF7FF47" authority="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela, 2022" authorityName="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela" authorityYear="2022" box="[277,534,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calafatiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FEDE5470FDF7FF47" box="[277,534,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Heteragrion calafatiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FDD15471FD88FF47" bold="true" box="[538,617,1570,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="389557BFFF818606FDD15471FD88FF47" box="[538,617,1570,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype from Pará, Brazil: (a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FC735414FA7CFF23" authority="DeMarmels, 1989" authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[952,1437,1606,1630]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorotaeniatum">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FC735414FB03FF23" box="[952,1250,1606,1630]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum</emphasis>
DeMarmels, 1989
</taxonomicName>
male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="59C8655DFF818601FF0C5487FDBBFC48" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF818606FF0C5487FEBDFEBA" blockId="3.[151,1437,1748,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FF0C5487FE31FF93" bold="true" box="[199,464,1748,1774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FE125486FD1AFF93" authority="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela, 2022" authorityName="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela" authorityYear="2022" box="[473,763,1748,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calafatiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FE125486FD1AFF93" box="[473,763,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Heteragrion calafatiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FCC85487FCBEFF93" bold="true" box="[771,863,1748,1774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="389557BFFF818606FCC85487FCBEFF93" box="[771,863,1748,1774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FC235486FB93FF93" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1000,1138,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FC235486FB93FF93" box="[1000,1138,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Heteragrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group B (
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FB3A5486FACEFF93" box="[1265,1327,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="75434B27FF818606FAF25487FF32FE6F" author="Lencioni, F. A. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="226" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref2568" refString="Lencioni, F. A. A. (2013) Diagnoses and discussion of the group 1 and 2 Brazilian species of Heteragrion, with descriptions of four new species (Odonata: Megapodagrionidae). Zootaxa, 3685 (1), 1 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3685.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Lencioni 2013</bibRefCitation>
), in which males possess an elongated paraproct. The morphologically closest species to 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FB7954AAFA83FE6F" authorityName="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela" authorityYear="2022" box="[1202,1378,1784,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calafatiensis">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FB7954AAFA83FE6F" box="[1202,1378,1784,1810]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">H. calafatiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FA4A54AAFDC9FE4B" authority="De Marmels, 1989" authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorotaeniatum">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FA4A54AAFEAEFE4B" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">H. chlorotaeniatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="75434B27FF818606FE9E554EFDC9FE4B" author="De Marmels, J." box="[341,552,1820,1847]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref2460" refString="De Marmels, J. (1989) Odonata or dragonflies from Cerro de la Neblina. Academia de las Ciencias Fisicas, Matematicas y Naturales, Caracas, Venezuela, 25, 1 - 78." type="journal article" year="1989">De Marmels, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and those two species can be separated by the following character combination (
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF818606FF6A5512FE9BFE27" authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[161,378,1856,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorotaeniatum">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF818606FF6A5512FE9BFE27" box="[161,378,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">H. chlorotaeniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): VbA absent (VbA present, 
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FCAE5513FC52FE26" box="[869,947,1856,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
), MP (
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FC355513FBACFE27" box="[1022,1101,1856,1882]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
) with rounded apex (MP with acute apex, 
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FED15537FE8BFE03" box="[282,362,1892,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
), ScP forming a small ridge bearing 4–5 denticles (
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FC555537FC0CFE03" box="[926,1005,1892,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
) in a single row (ScP forming a curved ridge bearing several teeth in a single row, 
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FD4F55DBFD37FEDF" box="[644,726,1928,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
), paraprocts (
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FCB955DBFC24FEDE" box="[882,965,1928,1955]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
) posteriorly oriented (paraprocts dorsally oriented, 
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF818606FECA55FFFEAEFEBA" box="[257,335,1964,1991]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[177,1413,196,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1546]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov., male holotypefrom Pará, Brazil:(a) head in dorsal view, (b) dorsal view of thorax, (c) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (d) terminal appendages in lateral view; Heteragrion chlorotaeniatum DeMarmels, 1989 male holotype from Río Negro, Venezuela: (e) terminal appendages in dorsal view, (f) terminal appendages in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405124" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405124/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="45AD665EFF868601FF5C511BFABCFA1C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405126" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6405126" box="[151,1373,840,865]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405126/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" startId="4.[151,250,840,864]" targetBox="[151,1437,181,816]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF868601FF5C511BFABCFA1C" blockId="4.[151,1373,840,865]" box="[151,1373,840,865]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF868601FF5C511BFEF2FA1D" bold="true" box="[151,275,840,864]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
Small stream in a forested shady area of Calafate village: type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF868601FBC9511AFAE7FA1D" authority="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela, 2022" authorityName="Mendoza-Penagos &amp; Juen &amp; Vilela" authorityYear="2022" box="[1026,1286,840,864]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calafatiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF868601FBC9511AFAE7FA1D" box="[1026,1286,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Heteragrion calafatiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="389557BFFF868601FAC7511AFABCFA1C" box="[1292,1373,841,865]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="116D36D6FF868601FF0C51E1FDBBFC48" blockId="4.[151,1437,946,1333]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF868601FF0C51E1FE25FAB0" bold="true" box="[199,452,946,973]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Habitat and Ecology.</emphasis>
The new species was found around 10:30 am, perched approximately 
<quantity id="D62A9B33FF868601FB2951E0FAEFFAB0" box="[1250,1294,947,973]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
high, on the branches that come off shrubs in a ravine along the banks of a small stream, in an Upland Forest shady area (
<figureCitation id="89E92A53FF868601FAA45184FF46FD68" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,840,864]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,181,816]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1437,181,816]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Small stream in a forested shady area of Calafate village: type locality of Heteragrion calafatiensis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405126/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Upland Forests are forests that develop in areas not subjected to flooding due to their location, mostly in higher regions of the Amazon relief (
<bibRefCitation id="75434B27FF868601FE15564CFD69FD44" author="Vicentini, A." box="[478,648,1055,1081]" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" pagination="143 - 177" refId="ref2697" refString="Vicentini, A. (2001) As Florestas de Terra Firme. In: Oliveira, A. A. &amp; Daly, D. (Eds.), Florestas do Rio Negro. Companhia das Letras, Sao Paulo, pp. 143 - 177." type="book chapter" year="2001">Vicentini 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The weather conditions on the collection day were very sunny, despite the little sun on the collection site. The vegetation is dominated by shrubs and medium-sized trees in that location. The stream bottom is mainly composed of sand and grass, clear water and a maximum depth of 
<quantity id="D62A9B33FF868601FB1F5634FAFCFDFC" box="[1236,1309,1127,1153]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
. Upstream, the environment in Calafate consists of a first-order stream (narrower than 
<quantity id="D62A9B33FF868601FC3356D8FBFAFDD8" box="[1016,1051,1163,1189]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" unit="m" value="1.0">1m</quantity>
) with slow current, with an open area in full sunlight, forming a small pool (approximately 
<quantity id="D62A9B33FF868601FCFD56FCFC46FDB4" box="[822,935,1199,1225]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" unit="cm" value="85.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="80.0">80–90 cm</quantity>
deep) with several macrophyte individuals. This portion of the stream is inhabited mainly by species from lentic environments such as: 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF868601FB575680FE87FC6C" authority="Williamson, 1916" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kennedii">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF868601FB575680FA7DFD90" box="[1180,1436,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Acanthagrion kennedii</emphasis>
Williamson, 1916
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D6D24D55FF868601FEBF56A4FC85FC6C" authority="(Burmeister, 1839)" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[372,868,1271,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Erythrodiplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castanea">
<emphasis id="23A6EAC4FF868601FEBF56A4FD9EFC6D" box="[372,639,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="227">Erythrodiplax castanea</emphasis>
(Burmeister, 1839)
</taxonomicName>
, 
